result.execSummary:
The defendant Aaron L Fountaine was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Fine to be paid at a rate of $50.00 per month commencing 11-15-2015; alternate 11 days jail.
Court finds defendant is not eligible for expunction.

records.addlTxt: with Elements of criminal offenses to which plea is being entered.

Defendant Aaron L Fountaine in court.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern Kelly Pingel appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant states he wishes to proceed today to plea and sentence without counsel.  Court performs colloquy with Defendant regarding waiving his right to counsel.  Defendant waives his right to counsel and again states he wishes to proceed unrepresented.  Defendant enters a no contest plea to Count #1.  Court performs colloquy with Defendant and finds Defendant guilty of Count #1. State gives sentencing recommendation.  Defendant makes statements.  Court sentences the Defendant to the following:

COUNT #1:  FINE:  $505.00 - to be paid at $50.00 per month, commencing 11/15/15, alternate 11 days jail if not paid. 

**Court finds  Defendant not eligible for expunction**
